{"type":"message","id":"d5fa4ff1","parentId":"70aa0a3c","timestamp":"2026-03-02T01:54:22.125Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"web_search:4","toolName":"web_search","content":[{"type":"text","text":"{\n  \"query\": \"OpenAI Meta Google latest AI model 2026\",\n  \"provider\": \"brave\",\n  \"count\": 8,\n  \"tookMs\": 1310,\n  \"externalContent\": {\n    \"untrusted\": true,\n    \"source\": \"web_search\",\n    \"provider\": \"brave\",\n    \"wrapped\": true\n  },\n  \"results\": [\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"210c5bd8ce529726\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAI Updates Today (February 2026) – Latest AI Model Releases\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"210c5bd8ce529726\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://llm-stats.com/llm-updates\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"afcf81f517a25ffd\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThis includes updates from OpenAI (GPT series, o-series), Anthropic (Claude), Google (Gemini), Meta (Llama), Mistral, DeepSeek, and other providers. Our timeline shows release dates, new capabilities, benchmark improvements, and feature additions for each version. Our API Provider Updates section tracks pricing changes, new features, rate limit updates, and API endpoint modifications for all major providers including OpenAI, Anthropic, Google Cloud AI, Azure OpenAI, Together AI, Fireworks, Groq, and more.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"afcf81f517a25ffd\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"3 days ago\",\n      \"siteName\": \"llm-stats.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"cd96a28dda48f7e0\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nNew AI Models Coming in 2026 and What They Do | Medium\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"cd96a28dda48f7e0\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://medium.com/@urano10/the-future-of-ai-models-in-2026-whats-actually-coming-410141f3c979\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"09391b1eb8a5313c\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nGemini 3.0 will roll out through Google Workspace (Docs, Sheets, Gmail), cloud services (Google Cloud), and direct consumer access through Google&#x27;s assistant interfaces. Meta&#x27;s next flagship open-source model, <strong>Llama 4,</strong> is expected in late 2025 ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"09391b1eb8a5313c\\\">>>\",\n      \"published\": \"January 16, 2026\",\n      \"siteName\": \"medium.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5875ed9a90956952\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMLQ.ai | AI for investors\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5875ed9a90956952\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://mlq.ai/news/meta-readies-nextgeneration-mango-and-avocado-ai-models-for-2026-launch/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e1578d13b3abe41c\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nMeta is preparing two next-generation artificial intelligence models, <strong>an image and video system known internally as “Mango” and a text-based large language model dubbed “Avocado,”</strong> with an internal roadmap targeting a launch in the first half of 2026, according to company documents and ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"e1578d13b3abe41c\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"mlq.ai\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5c03da0e37c0d7ee\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nModel Release Notes | OpenAI Help Center\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"5c03da0e37c0d7ee\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://help.openai.com/en/articles/9624314-model-release-notes\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"06389b877cceacda\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAs part of this update, the Extended thinking setting for <strong>GPT-5.2</strong> was unintentionally changed to be lower which we have now fixed. February 3, 2026: We made another small reduction to ...\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"06389b877cceacda\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"help.openai.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1562a764d8d7a9a5\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe best AI models in 2026: What model to pick for your use case | Pluralsight\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1562a764d8d7a9a5\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://www.pluralsight.com/resources/blog/ai-and-data/best-ai-models-2026-list\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"80ee3823df31c21c\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAnthropic’s Claude 4.5 is an agentic system designed to work &quot;autonomously for hours.&quot; And Google’s <strong>Gemini 2.5</strong> is a &quot;thinking model&quot; that dynamically allocates compute to reason through its thoughts before giving you an answer.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"80ee3823df31c21c\\\">>>\",\n      \"siteName\": \"www.pluralsight.com\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"title\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1ac9619177e39c13\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nThe billion-dollar infrastructure deals powering the AI boom | TechCrunch\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"1ac9619177e39c13\\\">>>\",\n      \"url\": \"https://techcrunch.com/2026/02/28/billion-dollar-infrastructure-deals-ai-boom-data-centers-openai-oracle-nvidia-microsoft-google-meta/\",\n      \"description\": \"\\n<<<EXTERNAL_UNTRUSTED_CONTENT id=\\\"ee224761b445dc18\\\">>>\\nSource: Web Search\\n---\\nAmazon was the capex leader, projecting $200 billion in 2026 spending (up from $131 billion in 2025), while Google was a close second with an estimate between $175 billion and $185 billion (up from $91 billion in 2025). Meta estimated $115 billion to $135 billion (up from $71 billion the previous year), although that figure is a little deceptive because a lot of the data center projects have been kept off their books entirely.\\n<<<END_EXTERNAL_UNTRUS